checkInputs(bytes32,uint256,bytes32).details: Use this for contracts that don't use submit/confirm functions, and which need to check provided inputs for accuracy before confirming a request. See TreasuryV3.sol for an example implementation.

confirmRequest(bytes32,address).details: Calling contract must provide the requestID and the address of the Admin calling it

params._adminAddress: Address of Admin calling the calling contract
params._requestID: Request ID of the multi-signature vote request

returns.requestApproved: Flag indicating if the request was approved (true) or is still pending (false), dependent contract uses this return value to determine when to process the function.

params._txnID: Transaction ID used by child contract for record-keeping

returns.requestID: Unique ID of multi-sig request, must be stored by child contract

checkInputs(bytes32,uint256,bytes32).notice: Returns true if provided inputs and transaction ID for the caller are correct for the request ID
